Email Marketing KPIs
Email remains one of the highest-ROI channels in B2B marketing. A 2026 analysis by HubSpot found that B2B email marketing continues to generate over forty dollars in return for every dollar spent when campaigns are properly segmented and personalized. But not all email KPIs are created equal.

Open Rate
Open rate is a baseline metric, but it has become less reliable since Apple's Mail Privacy Protection rollout inflated open rate numbers for many organizations. In 2026, savvy B2B marketers use open rate as a directional indicator alongside click-through rate and reply rate to get a more accurate picture of engagement.

What is a good open rate for B2B in 2026? Industry averages vary by sector, but a consistently deliverable, well-segmented B2B email list should see open rates between twenty and thirty percent. Below fifteen percent is a signal to revisit your subject lines, sending frequency, list hygiene, or all three.

Click-Through Rate (CTR)
CTR measures how many recipients clicked a link within your email. For B2B campaigns, a CTR between two and five percent is considered strong. If your open rate is healthy but your CTR is low, the problem is usually in your email body. Your content is not compelling readers to take the next step.

Email to Pipeline Contribution
This is the advanced metric that leadership actually cares about. How much pipeline, measured in dollar value, was sourced or influenced by email marketing? This requires tracking leads from email through to opportunity creation in your CRM. When you can show that email-sourced leads convert at a higher rate or shorter sales cycle than other channels, you build a compelling case for continued investment.

List Hygiene and Deliverability Rate
In 2026, deliverability is more critical than ever. Gmail, Outlook, and other major providers have tightened filtering algorithms. A deliverability rate below ninety-five percent is a red flag. Maintaining a clean list through regular hygiene, suppression of non-engaged contacts, and adherence to CAN-SPAM and GDPR requirements is a fundamental operational KPI that protects all your other email metrics.

Content Syndication KPIs
Content syndication is one of the most effective demand generation tactics in the B2B toolkit, particularly for reaching buyers in the research phase. But it requires precise measurement to ensure quality over quantity.

Lead Quality Score
Not all syndicated leads are equal. A lead quality score combines demographic fit (does this person match your ideal customer profile), firmographic fit (is this company in your target market), and behavioral signal (did they engage with content that indicates genuine purchase intent). Intent Amplify builds custom lead scoring models for clients that weight these factors based on historical conversion data, ensuring that the leads entering your funnel are genuinely worth the investment.

Content Engagement Depth
How far did the reader get through your content? Did they download the full asset, or did they abandon it after two pages? Content engagement depth tells you whether your content is genuinely meeting buyer needs or whether it is attracting downloads out of curiosity but failing to deliver value. This matters because high engagement depth correlates with higher downstream conversion rates.

Syndication Channel ROI
Different content syndication partners deliver vastly different results depending on your industry, target audience, and content type. Measuring ROI by syndication channel, tracking CPL, lead quality, and pipeline contribution for each partner separately, allows you to optimize your media mix in real time rather than waiting for end-of-quarter reporting.

Appointment Setting KPIs
For many B2B companies, appointment setting bridges the gap between marketing-generated interest and sales-driven conversations. It is a critical function that deserves its own set of KPIs.

Connection Rate
What percentage of outreach attempts result in a live conversation? In 2026, with voicemail filtering, email overload, and calendar gatekeeping more prevalent than ever, a strong connection rate requires a multi-touch, multi-channel approach. Intent Amplify's appointment setting programs use a combination of phone, email, and LinkedIn outreach, sequenced strategically to maximize connection rates with senior decision-makers.

Meeting Show Rate
Booking appointments is only half the battle. What percentage of booked meetings actually happen? A show rate below sixty percent suggests a problem with meeting relevance, too little time between booking and the meeting, or insufficient confirmation and reminder touchpoints. Best-in-class B2B appointment setting programs achieve show rates of seventy-five percent or higher.

Meeting to Opportunity Conversion Rate
This is the ultimate appointment setting KPI. How many meetings turn into qualified pipeline opportunities? If your show rate is strong but your meeting-to-opportunity rate is weak, the issue is likely in the qualification process before the meeting, meaning the wrong contacts are being booked, or in how your sales team conducts the first conversation.

